  "prompt": "What happened to Naughty America's face recognition tool?",
  "response": "Naughty America, an adult entertainment company, initially implemented a face recognition tool in 2016 to help users identify adult actors and find more of their content. However, the feature was quickly met with significant backlash due to privacy concerns and ethical implications. Many argued that such a tool could be misused to identify individuals without their consent, potentially leading to the exposure of people who did not wish to be identified in adult content.\n\nIn response to the criticism, Naughty America disabled the facial recognition feature shortly after its launch. The company acknowledged the concerns and stated that it would re-evaluate the tool's use and implications.\n\nSince then, there have been no reports of Naughty America reintroducing the facial recognition tool. The incident highlights the ongoing debate around the ethical use of facial recognition technology, especially in sensitive industries like adult entertainment.",
